				<div id="post-463" class="hentry p10 post publish author-canuckaholic category-work-examples tag-mysql-2 tag-php-2 tag-rhino tag-web-application is-full comments-closed pings-closed y2011 m05 d05 h13 alt slug-rhino-cup-run-2011"><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://popdigital.ca/2011/05/05/rhino-cup-run-2011/" title="Permalink to Rhino Cup Run 2011" rel="bookmark">Rhino Cup Run 2011</a></h2>
<div class="entry-meta"><span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">By </span><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://popdigital.ca/author/admin/" title="View all posts by Adrian">Adrian</a></span><span class="meta-sep meta-sep-entry-date"> | </span><span class="meta-prep meta-prep-entry-date">Published: </span><span class="entry-date"><abbr class="published" title="2011-05-05T20:46:58-0700">May 5, 2011</abbr></span></div><!-- .entry-meta -->
					<div class="entry-content">
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-468" title="rhino_cup_run_558x300" src="http://popdigital.ca/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/rhino_cup_run_558x300.jpg" alt="Rhino Cup Run 2011" width="558" height="300" /></p>
<h2>About:</h2>
<p>Rhino Cup Run 2011 is a web application built for Rhino Marketing Inc., a partner of the Vancouver Canucks. The application is a hockey pool where people can sign up, make game score predictions for each playoff round, and guess which Canucks players will finish with the most goals, most assists, etc. A winner is declared at the end of each round for the contestant with the highest score.</p>
<h2>Type of Project:</h2>
<p>Web Application. Built using a LAMP server architecture.</p>
<p><strong>URL:</strong> <a title="Rhino Cup Run 2011" href="http://rhino.ca/cuprun2011" target="_blank">rhino.ca/cuprun2011</a></p>
<h2>What We Did:</h2>
<div class="column">
<ul>
<li>HTML/XHTML</li>
<li>CSS</li>
<li>PHP</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="column">
<ul>
<li>Graphic Design</li>
<li>Javascript</li>
<li>MySQL</li>
</ul>
</div>
